Brazilian Stock Movers: Cyrela, Grupo Pao de Acucar, Tecnisa

-- B y   N e y   H a y a s h i
-- 
2011-07-13T14:20:23Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-13/brazilian-stock-movers-cyrela-grupo-pao-de-acucar-tecnisa.html
The following companies are having
unusual price changes in  Sao Paulo  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 9:58 a.m. New York time.
Preferred shares are usually the most-traded class of stock.  The Bovespa Index rose 1.3 percent to 60,459.47.  Cia. Brasileira de Distribuicao Grupo Pao de Acucar (PCAR4
BS) rose 1 percent to 65.66 reais after earlier dropping as much
as 2.2 percent. A proposal to merge the retailer with Carrefour
SA’s Brazilian unit fell through after  Brazil ’s government
withdrew financial support for the deal. Brazil’s national
development bank, known as BNDES, rejected a plan to help fund
the transaction with a 2 billion-euro ($2.8 billion) stake
purchase in the proposed new company, according to an e-mailed
statement yesterday.  Cyrela Brazil Realty SA Empreendimentos e Participacoes (CYRE3) 
(CYRE3 BS) gained 3 percent to 14.22 reais. Brazil’s second-
biggest homebuilder by revenue plans to repurchase as many as
21.2 million of its common shares within one year, according to
a regulatory filing.  Tecnisa SA (TCSA3)  (TCSA3 BS) rose 1.7 percent to 12.07 reais. The
Brazilian real-estate firm said in a filing contracted sales
more than doubled to 542.8 million reais in the second quarter
from a year earlier.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ney Hayashi in Sao Paulo at 
 ncruz4@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Papadopoulos in New York at 
 papadopoulous@bloomberg.net  